    public class MaterialModal
extends MaterialWidget
implements HasType<ModalType>, HasTransition, HasDismissable, com.google.gwt.event.logical.shared.HasCloseHandlers<MaterialModal>
    Dialogs are content that are not original visible on a page but show up with extra information if needed. The transitions should make the appearance of the dialog make sense and not jarring to the user.

    UiBinder Usage:

     <m:MaterialModal ui:field="modal" type="FIXED_FOOTER" dismissable="true" inDuration="500" outDuration="800">
     <m:MaterialModalContent>
         <m:MaterialTitle title="Title" description="Description" />
     </m:MaterialModalContent>
     <m:MaterialModalFooter>
         <m:MaterialButton text="Close Modal" type="FLAT"/>
     </m:MaterialModalFooter>
 </m:MaterialModal>
    *

    Java Usage:

     {
     @code
     @UiField
     MaterialModal modal;
     modal.openModal();
 }

    Author:
    kevzlou7979, Ben Dol
    See Also:
    Material Modals

    • Method Detail

      • openModal

        public void openModal()
        Open the modal programatically

        Note: the MaterialModal component must be added to the document before calling this method. When declaring this modal on a UiBinder file, the MaterialModal is already added, but if you call it using pure Java, you must add it to a container before opening the modal. You can do it by calling, for example: 

         MaterialModal modal = new MaterialModal();
 RootPanel.get().add(modal);
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the MaterialModal is not added to the document

      • closeModal

        public void closeModal()
        Close the modal programatically. It is the same as calling closeModal(boolean) with false as parameter.

        Note: you may need to remove it MaterialModal from the document if you are not using UiBinder. See openModal().

      • closeModal

        public void closeModal(boolean autoClosed)
        Close the modal programatically.

        Note: you may need to remove it MaterialModal from the document if you are not using UiBinder. See openModal().

        Parameters:
        autoClosed - Flag indicating if the modal was automatically dismissed
        See Also:
        CloseEvent
